"Since its high point in 1997, weâ€™ve lost two metres of water"  That's is insane.  I used to launch from Vic Harb.  I think that launch is not longer usable.    They where planning to dredge it, but I herd they are second guessing that now too...

I can find out on that pretty quick Nick... with Son working for the township.  Thing is.. all these people that bought "waterfront" in the last 40 years that are now high and dry, it wasn't waterfront originally. My wife grew up on Sturgeon Bay about the time she started pre-kindergarden, and her father still has a copy of the survey and they had 268 feet of front yard. When I was there for the first time in 1981 it was about 95 feet of front yard. Guess what... there is about 265 feet of front yard again...
Buy at high tide, sell at low tide.
